                            <comment id="13570162" author="ffang" created="Mon, 4 Feb 2013 13:46:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Benson,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think in some scenario cxf endpoint can handle request from local browser is useful, especially for some demos, let customer open a local browser and edit a soap message and send it out and see the response from same browser page is convenient.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For the CORS issue, I generally add a out interceptor for the cxf endpoint in demos, something like&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;EnableCORSInterceptor &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;extends&lt;/span&gt; AbstractPhaseInterceptor&amp;lt;Message&amp;gt; {

    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; EnableCORSInterceptor() {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;super&lt;/span&gt;(Phase.PRE_PROTOCOL);
    }

    @Override
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void handleMessage(Message message) &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; Fault {
        Map&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;, List&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; headers = Headers.getSetProtocolHeaders(message);
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//Access-Control-Allow-Origin:* Access-Control-Allow-Methods:POST,GET
&lt;/span&gt;            headers.put(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Access-Control-Allow-Origin&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, Arrays.asList(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;*&quot;&lt;/span&gt;));
            headers.put(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Access-Control-Allow-Methods&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, Arrays.asList(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;POST&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;GET&quot;&lt;/span&gt;));
        } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (Exception ce) {
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Fault(ce);
        }
    }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This can make browser send/receive soap message to/from CXF endpoint.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Freeman&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13570343" author="bmargulies" created="Mon, 4 Feb 2013 15:49:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;How does this prevent OPTIONS transaction from being processed by the subsequent interceptors?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13570807" author="ffang" created="Tue, 5 Feb 2013 00:49:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It won&apos;t. It just add some CORS headers to the response message so that  local browser can receive/recognize the response.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
